brainrotfilter (1.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix wizard permission error writing /etc/squid/squid.conf
    (LP: #1) configure_squid() now writes the desired snippet path to
    /var/lib/brainrotfilter/squid_include_path and triggers the new
    brainrotfilter-squid-apply.service (root oneshot) via systemctl
    start, permitted by debian/50-brainrotfilter.rules polkit rule.
    NoNewPrivileges=true in the main service prevented sudo from working.
  * Fix audio analysis always returning score=0
    - PYTHONPATH in brainrotfilter.service was pointing to
      src/brainrotfilter/ instead of src/, causing "import audio_analyzer"
      to resolve to None inside parallel_analyzer thread workers.
    - audio_analyzer.analyze() now accepts **_kwargs so callers may
      pass _whisper_model= without triggering a TypeError that was
      silently caught and converted to score=0.
    - Added shutil.which("ffmpeg") guard at startup; missing ffmpeg now
      logs a clear error instead of falling through with score=0.
  * Add scripts/apply_squid_config.sh privileged helper
  * Add debian/brainrotfilter-squid-apply.service root oneshot unit
  * Add debian/50-brainrotfilter.rules polkit rule
  * postinst: install polkit rule and enable squid-apply service

 -- IAmDestructoman <github@destructoman.dev>  Tue, 15 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000

brainrotfilter (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release
  * Ported from pfSense/FreeBSD to Linux (Debian/Ubuntu)
  * Replaced pfctl with conntrack for connection killing
  * Replaced SSH-based pfSense configurator with local Linux configurator
  * Uses openssl for CA certificate generation
  * Uses iptables for transparent proxy and QUIC blocking
  * Systemd service integration
  * Web-based setup wizard for Linux

 -- IAmDestructoman <github@destructoman.dev>  Sun, 12 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
